<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6599&amp;p=64214#p64214"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[SNES to NES joypad]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6599&amp;p=64214#p64214"><![CDATA[
There are a few practical problems with using Super NES controllers on an NES:<br /><ul><li>You need to solder up an adapter out of two controller extension cords, or you need to solder in pair of male and female DE-9 into your NES and Super NES controllers following the famiclone pinout. </li><li>Emulators are less likely to support it. Instead you have to use Four Score mode and map player 3's AXLR. They're even less likely to support the mouse. </li><li>If you're using DMC, you're more likely to run into bit deletions on sample fetches. </li></ul><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Jul 14, 2010 1:55 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
