Nope, but it could be possible with an adapter to use ONE port, and the state of the additional buttons A, X, L and R (NOTE : A "becomes" B and B "becomes" Y in the process or remapping the buttons, as they are the standard "jump" and "attack" for action games) would be output with more serial reads.<br /><br />Nintendo so obviously wanted it backwards compatible, but at a late point decided not to do so.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Wed Jul 14, 2010 12:04 pm</p><hr />
